                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 774/572.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Beaupré</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Hague</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1909-02-02">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 2, 1909</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 103.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to state that on receipt of the
                    department’s cablegram of the 27th ultimo,<note n="1" xml:id="d115fn1">See
                        telegram of Jan. 26 to Ambassador Reid.</note> I immediately advised the
                    minister for foreign affairs that the Governments of Italy and Austria-Hungary
                    had been invited to participate in the deliberations of the Internationl Opium
                    Conference at Shanghai and that his excellency has this day acknowledged the
                    receipt of said advice.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">A. M. Beaupré.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
